Privacy Policy
Last Updated:
Dec 17, 2024
This Privacy Policy describes Our policies and procedures on the collection, use, and disclosure of Your information when You use the Service and informs You about Your privacy rights and how the law protects You.
We use Your Personal Data to provide and improve the Service. By using the Service, You agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
Interpretation and Definitions
Interpretation
Words with initial capital letters have meanings defined under the following conditions. The following definitions apply regardless of whether they appear in singular or plural.
Definitions
Account
means a unique account created for You to access our Service or parts of it.
Affiliate
means any entity that controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with Us.
Application
means the software program
Shoppe - Shopping List
provided by Us on any electronic device.
Device
means any device such as a computer, cellphone, or digital tablet that can access the Service.
Personal Data
means information that identifies an individual.
Service
refers to the Application.
Service Provider
means a third-party company or individual that processes data on behalf of the Company.
Usage Data
means data collected automatically, such as how the Service is used.
You
means the individual using the Service or the legal entity they represent.
Collecting and Using Your Personal Data
Types of Data Collected
Personal Data
We may ask You to provide certain Personal Data that can be used to contact or identify You. This may include:
Usage Data
Usage Data
Usage Data is collected automatically and may include information like:
Your Device's IP address
Browser type and version
Pages visited, time spent, and date of access
Unique device identifiers
Diagnostic data
When accessing via a mobile device, additional data such as mobile device type, operating system, and unique ID may also be collected.
Use of Your Personal Data
We may use Your Personal Data to:
Provide and maintain Our Service
Manage Your Account
Fulfill contracts and process purchases
Contact You for updates, notifications, and security alerts
Send news, offers, and information (unless You opt out)
Manage and respond to Your requests
Analyze data and improve the Service
Evaluate business transfers like mergers or acquisitions
Retention of Your Personal Data
We retain Personal Data only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Policy. Usage Data may be retained for a shorter period unless required for security improvements or by law.
Transfer of Your Personal Data
Your information may be transferred to and maintained on servers outside Your country. By submitting Your information, You agree to such transfers under secure conditions.
Disclosure of Your Personal Data
We may disclose Your Personal Data in the following cases:
Business Transactions:
During a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets.
Law Enforcement:
If required by law or public authorities.
Legal Obligations:
To protect Our rights, property, or safety, and to prevent wrongdoing.
Security of Your Personal Data
We strive to protect Your Personal Data, but no method of transmission is 100% secure. While We use commercially acceptable methods, We cannot guarantee absolute security.
Children's Privacy
Our Service does not address users under 13. If You believe Your child has provided Personal Data, please contact Us to remove it.
Links to Other Websites
Our Service may contain links to third-party sites. We are not responsible for their content, policies, or practices. Review their Privacy Policies before use.
Changes to this Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy. You will be notified of changes via email or a prominent notice on Our Service. Updates become effective upon posting.
